### Anthias REST API — v2 Examples
### Use with the VS Code REST Client extension (humao.rest-client)
### Start dev server first: docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml up -d

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000
@contentType = application/json

# ─── Authentication ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# If auth is enabled, add: Authorization: Token <your-token>
# Generate with: docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml exec anthias-server
#   python manage.py drf_create_token <username>

# ─── Assets ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### List all assets
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/assets/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### Get a specific asset
# Replace <asset-id> with a real UUID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/assets/<asset-id>/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### Create an asset (URL-based)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/assets/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Test Web Page",
  "uri": "https://example.com",
  "mimetype": "webpage",
  "is_active": true,
  "is_enabled": true,
  "duration": 30,
  "play_order": 0
}

###

### Update an asset
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/assets/<asset-id>/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "is_active": false
}

###

### Delete an asset
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/assets/<asset-id>/

###

# ─── Playlists / Scheduling ───────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Get current playlist
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/assets/?is_active=true
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

# ─── System Info ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Get system info
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/info/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

### Get device settings
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v2/settings/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

###

# ─── OpenAPI Schema ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Download OpenAPI schema
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/schema/
Accept: application/yaml

###

### Browse API docs (Swagger UI)
# Open in browser:
# GET {{baseUrl}}/api/schema/swagger-ui/
